original_title: Dr. James Dobson, influential faith leader and advisor to five presidents, dies at 89 | Fox News
article_summary: Dr. James Dobson, influential Christian leader and founder of Focus on the Family, has died at 89. Dobson, a psychologist and former advisor to five U.S. presidents, was widely regarded as a pioneer who shaped generations' views on faith, family, and culture. His legacy includes growing Focus on the Family into one of the largest evangelical ministries in the world.</s>
